<h1>Privacy Policy for Light Muse</h1>
<p>Last updated: January 1, 2026</p>

<p>Light Muse (“we”, “our”, or “us”) values your privacy.  
This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our mobile application Light Muse.</p>

<h2>1. Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
<p>Light Muse does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, transfer, or share any personal data.  
Specifically, we do not collect:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Names or contact information</li>
    <li>Device identifiers</li>
    <li>Location data</li>
    <li>Photos, files, or media</li>
    <li>Usage analytics</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Local-Only Data</h2>
<p>Some app settings (such as theme, brightness, white noise preferences, or doodle content)  
are stored <strong>only on your device</strong> and never sent to any server.</p>

<h2>3. In-App Purchases</h2>
<p>Light Muse uses Apple’s official in-app purchase (IAP) system.  
We do not access or store your payment information.  
Apple handles all purchase processing securely.</p>

<h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>We may use Apple frameworks such as StoreKit or Firebase Remote Config (if configured).  
These services may collect non-identifiable diagnostics through Apple or Google following their own privacy policies.</p>

<h2>5. Children’s Privacy</h2>
<p>Light Muse does not target children and does not collect data from users of any age.  
Because no personal data is collected, parental consent is not required.</p>

<h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally.  
Your continued use of the app means you accept the updated policy.</p>

<h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> roy.niu.dev@gmail.com</p>

